At least 10,000 families will benefit from a National Hospital Insurance Fund(NHIF) cover paid for by the county government.
 A total of Sh125 million has been set aside for the medical cover, with Sh60 million planned for poor families and Sh65 million for county employees. 
 ALSO READ:

NHIF launches new medical scheme for police and prison officers

 Speaking during the launch of the programme in Saku Constituency, Governor Mohamud Ali announced plans to construct a Sh100 million medical training college in Marsabit town.





